We recommended the following:

a)	Concerned officers and employees who are using government vehicles properly accomplish the Driver’s Trip Tickets duly signed and approved by proper officials in order to strengthen the internal control on expenditures for fuel consumption which is vital in monitoring and determining the reasonableness of its expenditure;

b)	All drivers of the LGU vehicles to submit the Monthly Report of Official Travel.  Moreover, the General Services Officer, as the officer designated for the control of fuel consumption and report submission ensure that all drivers comply with the said requirement;

c)	Ensure that the Billing Statement submitted by the supplier is properly supported with appropriate document such as Copies of Gas Slips, delivery receipts or any similar documents, prior to acceptance. Require the supplier of fuel, oil and lubricant to attach this documents together with their Billing Statement for verification purposes; and

d)	Ensure that disbursement for fuel consumption is properly supported with proper and adequate documentation. Require concerned personnel to make payments based on verified documents to avoid over payment.

